        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/26473",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=doctorrock83",
                        "name": "doctorrock83",
                        "displayName": "julien PAULI",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Look at the RewriteRouter :\n{code}\n protected function _setRequestParams($request, $params)\n    {\n        foreach ($params as $param => $value) {\n\n            $request->setParam($param, $value);\n\n            if ($param === $request->getModuleKey()) {\n                $request->setModuleName($value);\n            }\n            if ($param === $request->getControllerKey()) {\n                $request->setControllerName($value);\n            }\n            if ($param === $request->getActionKey()) {\n                $request->setActionName($value);\n            }\n\n        }\n    }\n{code}\n\nI think that your idea is a router role, not an abstract request class role.\nActually we can retrieve the actual module\/contr\/action via _params array (and $this->_getParam() from an Action) just because the router tells that, in my opinion, the request shouldn't take care of that behavior.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=doctorrock83",
                        "name": "doctorrock83",
                        "displayName": "julien PAULI",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-11-18T12:42:59.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-11-18T12:42:59.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/26494",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "RewriteRouter already does this, and Julien is correct that this is a route and\/or router responsibility.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
